Text.Value: Bah. Every tinkerer thinks his toy is indestructible - until you hit it hard enough.
It shames me to admit this, but you must face this beast of Gondian folly alone - I would be crushed in an instant.
Did you help to construct this metal monstrosity, gnome? Help us disable it.
Indestructible? I'll reduce it to scrap metal before the day is done.
We're so close to the end - don't lose hope now.
Another battle. Just what I needed.
An over-confident appraisal. I'll show them the flaws in their design.
I hear it through the floor - powerful. Indestructible. The ultimate Watcher - the Titan.

EditorData.NodeContext: fear but also awestruck - he realises how amazing this is to have built

Text.Value: You don't understand what lies ahead!
Hope will not help us here, my friend.
Wait. Elevated gyroscopes, triple-set quadropecs. No - it can't be.

EditorData.NodeContext: Stops dead on wait as he cocks his head, listening intently. Lines in italics are rapid fire. Then horrified at end

Text.Value: Of course they built an indestructible super-Watcher. Why wouldn't they?
The Watcher tightens what? Whatever it be, Minsc will knock it loose.

EditorData.NodeContext: a bad bad pun where Minsc misunderstands the threat of the Watcher Titan

Text.Value: Fear not. Nothing is indestructible when nature's full fury is unleashed.
Move - we don't have time for this.
When it raises its shields, strike it with every scrap of magic and might you possess - and pray to Gond that it does not fire upon you. Good luck, my friend.

Synopsis: Fundango warns the player about the impending fight with the Titan.
